+# Operator Helm Chart
+
+This Helm chart deploys the AgentStream operator to a Kubernetes cluster.
+
+## Features
+
+- **Resource Prefix Support**: All Kubernetes resources can be prefixed to avoid naming conflicts when deploying multiple instances
+- **RBAC Integration**: Configurable RBAC roles and bindings
+- **Metrics Support**: Optional Prometheus metrics endpoint
+- **Certificate Management**: Optional cert-manager integration for TLS certificates
+- **Network Policies**: Optional network policies for metrics access control
+
+## Configuration
+
+### Global Settings
+
+```yaml
+global:
+  # Resource name prefix. If not set, defaults to the Helm release name.
+  # This prefix will be applied to all resource names to avoid conflicts
+  # when deploying multiple instances of the operator.
+  namePrefix: ""
+```
+
+### Controller Manager
+
+```yaml
+controllerManager:
+  replicas: 1
+  container:
+    image:
+      repository: controller
+      tag: latest
+    args:
+      - "--leader-elect"
+      - "--metrics-bind-address=:8443"
+      - "--health-probe-bind-address=:8081"
+```
+
+### RBAC
+
+```yaml
+rbac:
+  enable: true  # Enable RBAC resources
+```
+
+### Metrics
+
+```yaml
+metrics:
+  enable: true  # Enable metrics service
+```
+
+### Prometheus
+
+```yaml
+prometheus:
+  enable: false  # Enable ServiceMonitor for Prometheus
+```
+
+### Certificate Manager
+
+```yaml
+certmanager:
+  enable: false  # Enable cert-manager integration
+```
+
+### Network Policies
+
+```yaml
+networkPolicy:
+  enable: false  # Enable network policies
+```
+
+## Resource Prefix Examples
+
+### Default Behavior (No Prefix)
+
+When `global.namePrefix` is not set, resources will be named using the Helm release name:
+
+```bash
+helm install my-operator ./chart
+```
+
+This creates resources like:
+- `my-operator-operator-controller-manager` (Deployment)
+- `my-operator-operator-controller-manager-metrics-service` (Service)
+- `my-operator-operator-manager-role` (ClusterRole)
+
+### Custom Prefix
+
+When `global.namePrefix` is set, resources will use the custom prefix:
+
+```bash
+helm install my-operator ./chart --set global.namePrefix=prod
+```
+
+This creates resources like:
+- `prod-operator-controller-manager` (Deployment)
+- `prod-operator-controller-manager-metrics-service` (Service)
+- `prod-operator-manager-role` (ClusterRole)
+
+### Multiple Instances
+
+The prefix functionality allows you to deploy multiple instances of the operator without conflicts:
+
+```bash
+# Development instance
+helm install dev-operator ./chart --set global.namePrefix=dev
+
+# Production instance  
+helm install prod-operator ./chart --set global.namePrefix=prod
+
+# Staging instance
+helm install staging-operator ./chart --set global.namePrefix=staging
+```
+
+## Installation
+
+```bash
+# Basic installation
+helm install my-operator ./chart
+
+# With custom prefix
+helm install my-operator ./chart --set global.namePrefix=my-prefix
+
+# With custom values file
+helm install my-operator ./chart -f values.yaml
+```
+
+## Testing
+
+You can test the prefix functionality using the provided test values:
+
+```bash
+helm template test-operator ./chart -f test-prefix-values.yaml
+```
+
+This will generate Kubernetes manifests with the prefix "my-prefix" applied to all resource names. 
